In addition, the Bids and Awards Committee will ensure that the copies of cited documents (Mayor’s or Business Permit; Income Tax Returns (Annual Income Tax Return of the Preceding Tax Year) and original copy of the Omnibus Sworn Statement (OSS) that were not attached to the voucher will be submitted immediately.
Also, the provisions stipulated with the Local Budget Circular No. 125 dated April 7, 2020 that prescribes the exclusive use of the grant including the procurement of food assistance and other relief goods for the affected households in the period of enhanced community quarantine. All residents of Mataasnakahoy were affected due to the following reasons, to wit:
a. Means of public transportation have been suspended;
b. The lockdown prohibits people from going outside their homes except for getting necessities;
c. Public Market has been temporarily closed due to possible Covid-19 local transmissions;
d. Travel restrictions to nearby cities and municipalities have been observed;
e. Residents of Mataasnakahoy choose to stay at home due to scare of transmissions of corona virus;
f. Most businesses delivering essential functions in the municipality chose to shut down;
g. Many residents of Mataasnakahoy lost their job because of the temporarily closure of business or industries, refraining to report from duty, and restriction of other activities like agriculture and fisheries.
With the abovementioned observations, rest assured that the BAC, the Bids and Awards Committee will ensure that provisions of Government Procurement Policy Board (GPPB) Circular 01-2020 dated April 6, 2020 are fully complied with, particularly the documentary requirements; price negotiation and the online portal posting.
The Municipality will efficiently and effectively abide with the laws and provisions related to the implementation of social amelioration program like food assistance program as prescribed in Joint Memorandum Circular No. 1 series of 2020 of the Department of the Interior and Local Government (DILG), Department of Budget and Management (DBM), Department of Social Welfare and Development (DSWD), Department of Labor and Employment (DOLE), Department of Trade and Industry (DTI), Department of Agriculture (DA), and Department of Finance (DOF).
We would act upon on your objective insight for the betterment of the delivery of basic services.
